ey, Jr.]], American lawyer and politician, senior senator of Pennsylvania * 1960 &ndash; [[Olaf Ludwig]], German cyclist and manager * 1960 &ndash; [[Rudi Völler]], German footballer and manager *[[1961]] &ndash; [[Hiro Yamamoto]], American bass player and songwriter * 1962 &ndash; [[Hillel Slovak]], Israeli-American guitarist (d. 1988) *[[1963]] &ndash; [[Garry Kasparov]], Russian chess player and author *[[1964]] &ndash; [[Davis Love III]], American golfer and sportscaster * 1964 &ndash; [[Caroline Rhea]], Canadian actress and comedian * 1964 &ndash; [[John Swinney]], Scottish businessman and politician, [[Deputy First Minister of Scotland]] *[[1965]] &ndash; [[Patricio Pouchulu]], Argentinian architect and educator *[[1966]] &ndash; [[Ali Boumnijel]], Tunisian footballer * 1966 &ndash; [[Marc Ford]], American guitarist, songwriter, and producer *[[1967]] &ndash; [[Dana Barros]], American basketball player, coach, and sportscaster * 1967 &ndash; [[Michael Eisen]], American biologist and academic * 1967 &ndash; [[Olga Tañón]], Puerto Rican-American singer-songwriter *[[1968]] &ndash; [[Ted Washington]], American football player *[[1969]] &ndash; [[Dirk Muschiol]], German footballer *[[1970]] &ndash; [[Monty Brown]], American football player and wrestler * 1970 &ndash; [[Gerry Creaney]], Scottish footballer and manager * 1970 &ndash; [[Nick Garrett (bass-baritone)|Nick Garrett]], English singer * 1970 &ndash; [[Szilveszter Csollány]], Hungarian gymnast * 1970 &ndash; [[Ricardo Rincón]], Mexican-American baseball player * 1970 &ndash; [[Ricky Schroder]], American actor *[[1971]] &ndash; [[Franck Esposito]], French swimmer * 1971 &ndash; [[Danie Mellor]], Australian painter and sculptor * 1971 &ndash; [[Bo Outlaw]], American basketball player * 1971 &ndash; [[Valensia]], Dutch singer-songwriter, guitarist, and producer *[[1972]] &ndash; [[Mariusz Czerkawski]], Polish ice hockey player and golfer * 1972 &ndash; [[Aaron Lewis (musician)|Aaron Lewis]], American singer-so